<br>
If you use the appropriate illusion and alliance (I think that's a higher level one of what you'll use) you should be fine.   I was very paranoid so I would illusion, cast invis, run to target the turn in mobs and various people around them, run somewhere safe, break invis, and con them.  As long as everyone is dubious, you can then get close enough to cast alliance on them to bring the faction up enough to do the quest.<br>
<br>
Remember...illusion drops when you zone so if you are running around erudin and aren't real familiar with it, keep invis up as there are these transport pads...some cause zoneing and some don't.  I died in the erudin palace when I stepped on the wrong one and the illusion faded! :-)<br>
